Very good service and quick. They have a nice selection of ready to service foods for rice boxes. Ordered the imitation shark fin soup and fried intestine. Both are very good and fresh. Will try other dishes in the future.

I'm so glad to discover this place. Don't bother with the menu items, go inside and check out the off the menu dishes already prepared and for you to pick and choose. You can select 3 items and comes with rice and soup for $7.  Choices were limited when I got here at 5:00. I got the half braised duck which was packed and heavy for $12! When I get half a duck at other places, they omit the wing and lacking meat. The taste is delicious, almost as good as Bo Ky. I also got an entree size of the Thai sweet chilli fried chicken. The lady gave me all of it since it's close to closing. The flavor is really good, but the skin was no longer crispy. That's was expected, but it's really delicious. Also got the cooked broccoli and bok choy. Everything cost $22 and meals to last for days.

Don't be fooled by its dinky looks. The food is really good, especially the stuff that's off menu. They have the best Hong Kong style imitation shark's fin soup (a type of HK night market dish) that's basically the best in NYC but you won't find it on the menu. Prices are surprisingly cheap for what you get and Carol, the owner, really cares about her customers and the community. A rue hidden gem on the edge of Chinatown!

Very tiny old space. I saw people recommend this place for lunch combo or dish to take out.  I got fried  shishamo 炸多春魚 $8 and 豬耳 pig ears $7.5 Both dish was amazing. Everything is fresh made everyday. The deep fried fish they cook after I order so I wait about 10 mins there. I ate a few right away, Crispy outside, and seasoning was amazing!  definitely worth to wait!  While I was waiting, people start to line up to get lunch combo. Only $5.75 ! Pick 3 items and rice for around $5.  All the dishes are freshly cooked before lunch and laid out at the counter.  Everyday the selections vary, but generally have several different chicken, one or two fish, some pork, and various veggie tofu stir-fries.  Good place to get something quick.  Also, the lunch combo comes with a cup of Cantonese soup of the day.  If you are not into the pre-cooked selection at the counter, you can order from the menu.
